 context to show not only the effectiveness of nutritional approaches but also why nutrition is of fundamental importance to issues of world conservation. He has extended precepts of ruminant nutritional ecology to such distant adaptations as the giant panda and streamlined conceptual issues in a clearer logical progression, with emphasis on mechanistic causal interrelationships.Peter J. Van Soest is Professor of Animal Nutrition in the Department of Animal Science and the Division of Nutritional Sciences at the New York State College of Agriculture and Life Sciences, Cornell University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAnimal nutrition. 0aFeeds. 0aRumen fermentation. 0aRuminantsxFeeding and feeds. 4aGeneral Science. 4aNature Guides & Natural History.  aAnimal Behavior.  aAnimal Breeding.  aAnimal Diseases.  aAnimal Nutrition studies.  aAnimal Nutrition.  aAnimal Science class.  aAnimal Science student.  aAnimal Science studies.  aAnimal Science.  aAnimal behavior.  aAnimal care.  aAnimal diseases.  aAnimal genetics.  aagribusiness.  aanimal husbandry.  aapplied animal scientists.  aapplied veterinary medicine.  abasic ruminant nutrition.  abiology of ruminants.  abooks about taking care of farm animals.  adigestive physiology.  afarm animal care.  afarm animal studies.  afarm animal vet.  afarm animal veterinary medicine.  afeed science.  afeeding ruminants.  agraduate animal studies students.  ahusbandry reference book.  alarge animal veterinary.  amammal zoology.  anonruminant herbivorous.  aruminant husbandry.  aruminant nutrition and metabolism.  aruminant nutrition.  aruminant nutritional ecology.  athe ruminant animal.  aupper division animal science undergraduates.  aveterinary medicine.  aveterinary science.08iTitle is p